// Figure 3.4: Place Order Saga - Sequence Diagram
// Client → Gateway → Basket → RabbitMQ → Ordering

// ==================== ACTORS ====================
Client [icon: user, color: blue]
Ocelot Gateway [icon: aws-api-gateway, color: orange]
Basket Service [icon: shopping-cart, color: green]
RabbitMQ [icon: rabbitmq, color: yellow]
Ordering Service [icon: clipboard-list, color: purple]
SQL Server [icon: mssql, color: red]
Redis [icon: redis, color: green]

// ==================== SYNCHRONOUS PHASE ====================
Client > Ocelot Gateway : POST /Basket/Checkout
Ocelot Gateway > Basket Service : Route to /api/v1/Basket/Checkout
Basket Service > Redis : GetBasketByUserNameQuery
Basket Service > RabbitMQ : Publish BasketCheckoutEvent
Basket Service > Redis : DeleteBasketByUserNameCommand
Basket Service > Ocelot Gateway : 202 Accepted
Ocelot Gateway > Client : 202 Accepted

// ==================== ASYNCHRONOUS PHASE ====================
RabbitMQ > Ordering Service : Consume BasketCheckoutEvent
Ordering Service > Ordering Service : Map + Validate
Ordering Service > SQL Server : INSERT Order
